cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with saliency prediction in videos using convolutional neural networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with 360-degree videos, which are a form of multimedia. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes a weakly-supervised training method for the network. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with developing a network for automatic saliency prediction. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with rendering 360-degree views on a cube using perspective projection.
